#1a
setwd("~/Downloads")
df <- read.csv("Nurses.csv", as.is=TRUE)
for(i in 1:1000){
  if(df$hospsize[i] == "small"){
    df$size_num[i] = 0
  }else if(df$hospsize[i] == "medium"){
    df$size_num[i] = 1
  }else if(df$hospsize[i] == "large"){
    df$size_num[i] = 2
  }
} 

#1b
df$Chospsize = df$size_num - 1 
#1c
for(i in 1:1000){
  if(df$wardtype[i] == "general care"){
    df$Nwardtype[i] = 0
  }else if(df$wardtype[i] == "special care"){
    df$Nwardtype[i] = 1
  } 
}
#1d
for(i in 1:1000){
  if(df$expcon[i] == "control"){
    df$Nexpcon[i] = 0
  }else if(df$expcon[i] == "experiment"){
    df$Nexpcon[i] = 1
  } 
}
#1e
df$Cexpcon = df$Nexpcon - 0.5
#1f
df$Cage = df$age - mean(df$age)
#1g
df$Cexperience = df$experience - mean(df$experience)
#Sort the data by school then by class then subject within class

library(ggplot2)

df.s <- df[order(df$hospital,df$ward,df$nurse),]
#df.s
library(nlme)
ctrl <- lmeControl(opt='optim')#np55d to increase number of iterations during 
m1 <- lme(stress ~1+Chospsize+Nwardtype+Cexpcon+Cexpcon*Chospsize+gender+
            Cexperience+Cage, random = ~ 1|hospital/ward, #put higher level BEFORE/ and lower level AFTER /
          data=df.s, na.action=na.omit, method="ML", control=ctrl)

ICC measure the reliability of ratings in studies where there are two or more raters.

icc23 = 0.5845884 means moderate Intraclass correlation means moderate reliability.

icc3 = 0.2625374 means poor Intraclass correlation means moderate reliability.
